### What was completed 2026-07-13 (Claude Code — Whole-site design improvement pass)
Approved plan executed across all 9 pages (see JOURNAL for detail):
- **Fonts fixed site-wide:** all 8 subpages were loading dead Plus Jakarta Sans and rendering fallback sans-serif; now load the Typekit Navigo kit like index.html.
- **Design language unified:** squared `.mcs-card`/`.mcs-gallery-card`/`.service-card`/`.category-card`/`.stat-pill`/`.testimonial-card` (radius 0); interior section rhythm 80→88px.
- **POLICY CHANGE (Matt-approved):** Unsplash stand-in imagery is now allowed as placeholder treatment. All 53 interior `.img-placeholder` divs replaced with curated `<img>` stand-ins (only the 17 verified homepage URLs reused; credit + "awaiting client photo" HTML comment on each). FANUC badge placeholder untouched.
- **Responsive:** mobile nav switch moved 768→1000px (header needs ~975px; logo no longer crushes), hero 480px@768/440px@480, section padding 64/56 on mobile, news cards stack @480, alert banner shows HQ number only @480, machine-browse breakpoints normalized to 1024/640.
- **A11y:** global `:focus-visible` (orange outline), skip-to-content link in header partial (`#main` id on every page), `prefers-reduced-motion` (CSS + JS guards; autoplay off), carousel dots get `aria-selected`, off-screen slides `aria-hidden` + links tabindex -1, autoplay pauses on hover/focus, duplicate `role="banner"` removed from alert banner, homepage h1 added (slide 1 headline), hero LCP img now eager/fetchpriority=high, news thumbs have width/height.
- **Polish:** unified card hover (lift + shadow) across all card types, image zoom-on-hover in card shells, staggered scroll-reveal (60ms cascade), about.html inline-styled headline → `.section-title`/`.section-body`, `es-hero__headline--md` modifier replaces inline h1 font-sizes (fixed 390px overflow on about/support).
- **Verified (Playwright, Chromium):** all 9 pages × 4 widths — zero console errors, zero failed requests, Navigo loads everywhere, no horizontal overflow, keyboard pass (skip link first tab stop, 2px focus outline), reduced-motion pass (no autoplay, no hidden content).

### Previously completed 2026-07-13 (Claude Code — "Gerotech Homepage.dc.html" alignment pass)
Implemented the homepage redesign spec from the Deep Code export ("Gerotech Homepage - Standalone.html" in ~/Downloads, unpacked from its bundler format). Most of the design was already in place from the earlier Figma integration; this pass closed the gaps:
- **Logos:** extracted the two logo SVGs shipped in the design bundle → `assets/images/gerotech-logo.svg` (dark, header, 30px) and `gerotech-logo-white.svg` (footer, 28px). Header now uses the SVG (was PNG); footer wordmark text replaced with the white SVG image.
- **Hero slider:** converted from crossfade to design-spec sliding track (`.hero-slider__track`, translateX, 0.45s cubic-bezier). Slides 2–6 now use the design's dashed "Slide N — Placeholder / Awaiting client copy" box (`.slide--placeholder`, `.slide__ph`) with lighter overlay; removed made-up eyebrows. `.slide__bg` fixed for real `<img>` (object-fit: cover). Autoplay 6s (design default). Dots: bottom 22px, gap 9px.
- **Testimonials:** homepage carousel now slides (new `.testimonial-carousel__track--slide` + `.testimonial-carousel__row`; ES page cards variant unchanged). Squared edges per design (radius removed), panel padding 60/52, photo min-height 420px, quote mark 56px/900. Inactive dot color → new token `--clr-gray-dot` (#C9C9D2).
- **News:** thumbs 132×94 square (was 120×88 r10), title 18px/700, excerpt 14px max-width 720px, meta tracking 0.08em, row padding 24px.
- **CTA band:** card max-width 940px (was 1044), headline max-width 460px / lh 1.18 / balance.
- **Email signup:** section gap 8px, sub margin-bottom 18px, input 13×16 with new token `--clr-gray-input` (#D6D6D6), submit 13×22.
- **Intro:** machines block margin-top 88px per design.
- **Verified** with Playwright (Chromium, 1440px + 390px): slider/testimonial motion, logo rendering, all sections, no console errors.
- **DECISION — fonts:** the .dc.html spec uses Archivo + IBM Plex Sans, but the repo was deliberately switched to Navigo (Adobe Fonts/typekit) after that export (brand standards). Kept Navigo via the existing `--font-display`/`--font-sans` tokens. Flag to Matt if the design fonts should win.

